## Incident Response Phases

## Phase 1: Detection and Analysis

### Detection Sources

- [ ] Security monitoring alerts (SIEM, IDS/IPS)
- [ ] Log analysis and anomaly detection
- [ ] User reports
- [ ] Third-party notifications (vendors, researchers)
- [ ] Vulnerability scans
- [ ] Threat intelligence feeds
- [ ] Customer reports

### Initial Analysis Checklist

- [ ] Confirm incident is real (not false positive)
- [ ] Determine incident severity
- [ ] Identify affected systems and data
- [ ] Assess immediate risks
- [ ] Document initial findings
- [ ] Activate incident response team
- [ ] Begin incident timeline

### Detection Response Actions

```typescript
// Example: Automated alert routing
export async function handleSecurityAlert(alert: SecurityAlert) {
  // 1. Log the alert
  await logSecurityEvent({
    eventType: SOC2EventType.SECURITY_ALERT,
    severity: mapAlertSeverity(alert.severity),
    action: 'Security alert received',
    outcome: 'success',
    ipAddress: alert.sourceIp,
    metadata: alert,
  });

  // 2. Assess severity
  const severity = assessIncidentSeverity(alert);

  // 3. Notify appropriate team members
  if (severity === 'CRITICAL' || severity === 'HIGH') {
    await notifyIncidentTeam(severity, alert);
  }

  // 4. Create incident ticket
  const incident = await createIncidentTicket({
    severity,
    description: alert.description,
    affectedSystems: alert.affectedSystems,
  });

  return incident;
}
```

